.TH "BSON_STRNCPY" "3" "2016\(hy02\(hy04" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_strncpy() \- Copies up to size bytes from src into dst. dst must be at least size bytes in size. A trailing \0 will be set.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
void
bson_strncpy (char       *dst,
              const char *src,
              size_t      size);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B
.B dst
The destination buffer.
.LP
.TP
.B
.B src
The src buffer.
.LP
.TP
.B
.B size
The number of bytes to copy into dst, which must be at least that size.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Copies up to
.B size
bytes from
.B src
into
.B dst
\e&.
.B dst
must be at least
.B size
bytes in size. A trailing
.B \e0
will be set.


